The '''NHIF Ambulance Scandal''' is a scandal relating to irregularities in purchase of ambulances for the [[National Hospital Insurance Fund]] of [[Kenya]] in 2001.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://allafrica.com/stories/200112310121.html|title=Kenya: The Ambulance Saga That Cost Minister His Job|first=Lucy|last=Ndichu|date=31 December 2001|website=Allafrica.com|accessdate=19 October 2017}}</ref>
The scandal resulted in the sacking of the Minister of Medical Services [[Amukowa Anangwe]] by President [[Daniel arap Moi]].
